
{{alias}}( x, λ, k )
    Evaluates the logarithm of the cumulative distribution function (CDF) for a
    Weibull distribution with scale parameter `λ` and shape parameter `k` at a
    value `x`.

    If provided `NaN` as any argument, the function returns `NaN`.

    If provided a nonpositive value for `λ` or `k`, the function returns `NaN`.

    Parameters
    ----------
    x: number
        Input value.

    λ: number
        Scale parameter.

    k: number
        Shape parameter.

    Returns
    -------
    out: number
        Evaluated logCDF.

    Examples
    --------
    > var y = cdf( 2.0, 1.0, 1.0 )
    ~-0.145
    > y = {{alias}}( -1.0, 2.0, 2.0 )
    -infinity
    > y = {{alias}}( {{alias:@stdlib/math/constants/float64-pinf}}, 4.0, 2.0 )
    0.0
    > y = {{alias}}( {{alias:@stdlib/math/constants/float64-ninf}}, 4.0, 2.0 )
    -infinity
    > y = {{alias}}( NaN, 0.0, 1.0 )
    NaN
    > y = {{alias}}( 0.0, NaN, 1.0 )
    NaN
    > y = {{alias}}( 0.0, 0.0, NaN )
    NaN
    > y = {{alias}}( 2.0, 0.0, -1.0 )
    NaN


{{alias}}.factory( λ, k )
    Returns a function for evaluating the logarithm of the cumulative
    distribution function (CDF) of a Weibull distribution with scale parameter
    `λ` and shape parameter `k`.

    Parameters
    ----------
    λ: number
        Scale parameter.

    k: number
        Shape parameter.

    Returns
    -------
    logcdf: Function
        Logarithm of Cumulative distribution function (CDF).

    Examples
    --------
    > var mylogcdf = {{alias}}.factory( 10.0, 2.0 );
    > var y = mylogcdf( 12.0 )
    ~-0.27
